      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 32-year-old teacher from Mumbai attends a health workshop aimed at understanding the basics of health care systems. During a group discussion, she realizes that her perception of health care might be limited, basing it only on her experiences with hospitals and clinics. The facilitator of the workshop provides a series of statements to the attendees for further clarification.Which of the following statements is most incorrect regarding the concept of health care?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2017040",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34825,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. A. Medical care is synonymous with health care.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A:</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Health care&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">encompasses a <strong>broad range</strong> of <strong>services</strong> that go beyond <strong>medical care.</strong> While <strong>medical care</strong> is a <strong>critical component</strong>, <strong>health care</strong> also includes <strong>preventive care, public health initiatives, health education, rehabilitation</strong> <strong>services,</strong> and <strong>mental health care</strong>, among others. It&#39;s a <strong>comprehensive concept</strong> that addresses the overall <strong>physical, mental</strong>, and <strong>social well-being</strong> of individuals and communities<strong>, not</strong> just the <strong>treatment</strong> of illnesses or medical conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Explanation</span></u></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option&nbsp;B.&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">The purpose of health care, including promoting, maintaining, monitoring, or restoring health:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"> &nbsp;Is a <strong>correct</strong> and encompassing<strong> definition</strong> of the <strong>goals</strong> of <strong>health care</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Option&nbsp;C.</strong>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Health care is a public right:</strong> The view of <strong>health care</strong> as a <strong>public right</strong> varies by <strong>region </strong>and <strong>political perspective</strong>, but it is <strong>increasingly </strong>recognized as a fundamental aspect of <strong>societal wellbeing</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option&nbsp;D.</span></strong> <span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>Medical care range from domiciliary care to resident hospital care</strong><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><strong>Medical care</strong> does indeed range from <strong>domiciliary (in-home) care</strong> to <strong>resident hospital care,</strong> covering a <strong>wide spectrum of services</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/08/13/screenshot-2024-08-13-092402.png\" style=\"height:532px; width:1000px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ref</span></u></strong><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 980</span></strong></span></span></p>",
